<paragraph id="833A7115FFED146F68DED3074F934094" blockId="14.[136,786,279,431]" pageId="14" pageNumber="235">
and irregularly reflexed), ciliate with straight well-separated hairs, both surfaces glabrous or glabrate; sepal glands shortpubescent; filaments 
<quantity id="447DDCF0FFED146F693FD3474E814055" box="[361,488,342,367]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.5 mm</quantity>
, glabrous; ovary moderately pubescent with thick straight hairs; styles 4, c. 
<quantity id="447DDCF0FFED146F6A27D3674DA840B5" box="[625,705,375,399]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
, basally pubescent.
</paragraph>
